{
  "local_port": 44268,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is your advice for a 25 year old guy who is broken and see no hope in his future?",
  "response": "At 25, it\u2019s completely normal to feel lost, overwhelmed, or even broken at times. Life is a journey with ups and downs, and feeling this way doesn\u2019t mean your future is without hope. Here\u2019s some advice to help you move forward:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - **It\u2019s okay to feel broken.** You\u2019re human, and emotions are part of the human experience. Don\u2019t suppress your feelings\u2014acknowledge them and understand that they don\u2019t define your future.\n   - Journaling or talking to someone you trust can help you process your emotions.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Take Small Steps**\n   - When everything feels overwhelming, focus on small, manageable steps. Progress doesn\u2019t have to be huge\u2014it just needs to be consistent.\n   - Set tiny, achievable goals each day, like getting out of bed, going for a walk, or completing one task. Celebrate these small wins.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Focus on Self-Care**\n   - **Physical health:** Eat nutritious food, exercise (even a short walk counts), and get enough sleep. Physical well-being impacts mental health.\n   - **Mental health:** Practice mindfulness, meditation, or deep breathing to calm your mind.\n   - **Emotional health:** Spend time with people who make you feel valued and supported.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Challenge Negative Thoughts**\n   - When you feel hopeless, your mind might exaggerate the worst-case scenarios. Ask yourself: *\u201cIs this thought 100% true? What evidence do I have that things won\u2019t get better?\u201d*  \n   - Replace negative self-talk with affirmations like, *\u201cI\u2019m doing the best I can, and that\u2019s enough.\u201d*\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Seek Support**\n   - You don\u2019t have to face this alone. Reach out to friends, family, or a therapist. Talking to a professional can provide tools and perspectives to help you rebuild.\n   - Support groups or online communities can also be helpful if you feel isolated.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Reconnect with Your Passions**\n   - Think about activities or hobbies that once brought you joy. Even if you don\u2019t feel like doing them now, start small. Reconnecting with what you love can reignite a sense of purpose.\n   - If you\u2019re unsure of your passions, try something new. Experimentation can lead to unexpected discoveries.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Focus on Growth, Not Perfection**\n   - Life isn\u2019t about being perfect\u2014it\u2019s about growth. Mistakes and setbacks are part of the process. Learn from them and keep moving forward.\n   - Remember, your worth isn\u2019t tied to your achievements or current circumstances.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Find Meaning**\n   - Reflect on what truly matters to you. What kind of person do you want to be? What kind of impact do you want to have on the world? Even small acts of kindness can give life meaning.\n   - Consider volunteering or helping others. Helping someone else can provide a sense of purpose and perspective.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Give Yourself Time**\n   - Healing and rebuilding take time. Be patient with yourself. Your future isn\u2019t set in stone\u2014every day is a chance to create something new.\n   - Remember, some of the most successful people didn\u2019t find their path until later in life.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Believe in the Possibility of Change**\n   - It\u2019s hard to see hope when you\u2019re in the middle of pain, but life is full of possibilities. Things won\u2019t stay the same forever. You have the power to create a different future, one step at a time.\n\n---\n\nYou\u2019re stronger than you think, and this difficult moment doesn\u2019t define your entire life. Take it one day at a time, and remember: **there\u2019s always hope, even if you can\u2019t see it yet.** You\u2019ve got this. \ud83d\udcaa\u2728",
  "temperature": 1.0,
